OL,3,CNo extra homes to be used for asylum
OL,4,Cseekers following city's housing crisis
OL,6,FClearsprings Ready Homes has said it
OL,7,Fwill not be looking for additional
OL,8,Fasylum dispersal accommodation in
OL,9,FPortsmouth and instead plans to
OL,10,Fmaintain and manage the number of
OL,11,Fproperties it currently uses in the
OL,12,Fcity.
OL,14,FThe latest available data shows that
OL,15,Fin June 2025, the Government was
OL,16,Fhousing 617 people seeking asylum in
OL,17,Fdispersal accommodation in Portsmouth.
OL,18,FThis is in line with the average
OL,19,Fnumber over the last two years.
